data.description:
NFL football, country music and Elizabeth Warren at one time! Be still my racing heart! The NFL DRAFT is happening in downtown Nashville with 300,000 🏈fans getting their groove on over 3 days! 

The plan is, within the stringent, heightened security rules, to connect with 
as many 🏈fans as possible to spread our 💘 for Elizabeth and her "I've 
Got a Plan For That"  platform. If we all wear our favorite Elizabeth 👕and buttons, I'm positive we can engage hundreds of future Warren supporters! They can Text FIGHT to 24477 to get hooked up with the campaign.

Tim McGraw is playing a free concert Friday night and Dierks Bentley is playing on Saturday night. Other artists are playing through the event as well.

I'll be available both days by text to answer questions and provide support. We may try to arrange a get-together, perhaps for lunch on both days.
data.title: Win with Warren Nashville NFL Blitz!

Join us for the first ever Warren's with Women event right here in Cedar Rapids to learn a new  skill from Molly Monk, hear from organic farmer Corbin Scholz who started up Rainbow Roots Farm, and mingle with other women & nonbinary people who are dreaming big and fighting hard! 

Elizabeth is all about empowering women and young girls, and she strongly believes in the power of people to achieve whatever they want if they persist. And we're so excited to start up this monthly event to live that value locally! 

If you have any accessibility needs, please let Lorraine (they/them) know by emailing lwong@elizabethwarren.com or calling/texting (319)382-0615 so that we can make sure the event will be accessible and comfortable for you. Children extremely welcome.

data.description:
Join us at the Wellington Heights neighborhood clean-up, hosted by the Wellington Heights Neighborhood Association, to care for our home and meet other community members!

Our team knows that to create real change – to rebuild the middle class and save our democracy – we need to dream big and fight hard. That's why we’re in this fight: to have real conversations about how to level the playing field for working families, who is best to lead that fight, and how to do that on a local level through grassroots work right in our own communities. 

WHNA has set the schedule as: 
8 am - Breakfast!
9 am - #1Bagchallenge litter & bulky branch pick-up 
11 am - Lunch!

If you have any accessibility needs, please let Lorraine (they/them) know by emailing lwong@elizabethwarren.com or calling/texting (319)382-0615 so that we can make sure the event will be accessible and comfortable for you. This neighborhood clean-up does mostly include trash pick-up, so if walking for ~2 hours is difficult for you, we'll help find you another way to be involved in the clean-up! 

We’ll see you there! Thanks for being a part of this fight.
data.title: Team Warren at Wellington Heights Neighborhood Clean-up
